                    <h4>📚 Why Timeline Matters</h4>
                    <p>Your brain didn't randomly decide to create pain. It learned to protect you during a specific time of threat or overwhelm. By identifying when pain started and what was happening in your life, you see the pattern: emotional danger → brain creates physical protection.</p>
                    
                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <strong>Common Pattern:</strong> "My pelvic pain started 6 months after my divorce/mom got sick/I took on caregiving/work became unbearable." The delay is normal - your brain held on as long as it could before creating a physical outlet for emotional overwhelm.
                    </div>
