                    <div class="exercise-item">
                        <div class="exercise-header">
                            <span class="exercise-title">First Real Pelvic Somatic Tracking</span>
                            <span class="exercise-time">10 min</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <p><strong>The moment you've been building toward - you're ready!</strong></p>
                            
                            <div class="provocative-box" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8f4f8, #d1ecf1); border-color: #17a2b8;">
                                <h5 style="color: #0c5460;">Your First Pelvic Tracking Session</h5>
                                
                                <p><strong>Preparation (2 min):</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Sit or lie comfortably</li>
                                    <li>Hand on heart: "I am safe"</li>
                                    <li>3 deep breaths</li>
                                    <li>Remember: Sensations can't hurt you</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Warm-up (2 min):</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Track hands for 30 seconds (safe zone)</li>
                                    <li>Track shoulders for 30 seconds</li>
                                    <li>Track lower back for 30 seconds</li>
                                    <li>Track hips for 30 seconds</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>The Main Event (60 seconds only!):</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Bring gentle awareness to pelvic area</li>
                                    <li>Whatever you notice: "Hello, I see you"</li>
                                    <li>Rate intensity 1-10</li>
                                    <li>Observe: Is it moving? Pulsing? Changing?</li>
                                    <li>Add lightness: "You're working so hard to protect me"</li>
                                    <li>After 60 seconds, return to hands</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Cool-down (2 min):</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Return to tracking hands</li>
                                    <li>3 deep breaths</li>
                                    <li>Say: "I did it. I observed without catastrophe."</li>
                                    <li>This is a HUGE victory!</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="checkbox-wrapper">
                                <input type="checkbox" id="day15-pelvic">
                                <label for="day15-pelvic">Completed first pelvic somatic tracking!</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="exercise-item">
                        <div class="exercise-header">
                            <span class="exercise-title">Evening Endo Affirmation</span>
                            <span class="exercise-time">5 min</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <p>Write in your journal:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>"I have endometriosis AND my nervous system amplifies it"</li>
                                <li>"The endo might be a 3, but my brain makes it a 12"</li>
                                <li>"I can reduce the amplification while still treating the condition"</li>
                                <li>"Even 50% less amplification would change my life"</li>
                                <li>"Today I proved I can observe pelvic sensations safely"</li>
                            </ul>
                            
