                    <span class="day-title">Day 18: Dialogue with Pain as Protector</span>
                    <span class="day-date">Week 3, Day 4</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="day-theme">
                    <h4>Today's Focus: Understanding What Your Pain is Protecting You From</h4>
                    <p>Having a compassionate conversation with your symptoms.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="education-section">
                    <h4>📚 Your Pain is Not Your Enemy</h4>
                    <p>Your pain is like an overprotective bodyguard who thinks you're constantly in danger. It showed up during a difficult time to protect you from emotional overwhelm. By talking to it with curiosity rather than hatred, you can understand its purpose and negotiate a new relationship.</p>
                    
                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <strong>IFS Principle:</strong> Every symptom is a "part" trying to help you. When you understand what it's protecting you from, you can address the real issue and the protection (pain) becomes unnecessary.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="exercises-section">
                    <h4>Today's Exercises</h4>
                    
                    <div class="exercise-item">
                        <div class="exercise-header">
