                            <span class="exercise-time">20 min</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <div class="ifs-dialogue-box">
                                <h5>Conversation with Your Pain</h5>
                                
                                <p><strong>Preparation:</strong> Get comfortable, hand on pelvis, breathe deeply</p>
                                
                                <div class="question">
                                    <p><strong>You:</strong> "Hello, pelvic pain. I know you're trying to help me. What are you protecting me from?"</p>
                                    <p><em>Listen for the answer - it might be: from feeling emotions, from sexual vulnerability, from saying no, from others' demands...</em></p>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="question">
                                    <p><strong>You:</strong> "When did you first arrive to protect me?"</p>
                                    <p><em>Often connects to your timeline from Day 15 - during divorce, illness, overwhelming responsibility...</em></p>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="question">
                                    <p><strong>You:</strong> "What are you afraid would happen if you weren't so loud?"</p>
                                    <p><em>Listen - might be: you'd ignore your needs, you'd be vulnerable, you'd have to face difficult emotions...</em></p>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="question">
                                    <p><strong>You:</strong> "I appreciate you trying to protect me. What if we found a gentler way? What would you need to feel safe turning down the volume?"</p>
                                    <p><em>This opens negotiation - maybe it needs you to set boundaries, express anger, take breaks...</em></p>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="question">
                                    <p><strong>You:</strong> "Thank you for talking with me. I'm listening now. We can work together."</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Journal what you discovered:</strong> "My pain is protecting me from ___. It first arrived when ___. It needs ___ to feel safe reducing intensity."</p>
                            
