                <div class="education-section">
                    <h4>📚 Why Imagination First?</h4>
                    <p>Your brain can't tell the difference between vividly imagined and real experiences. By repeatedly imagining triggers with safety and joy, you're literally rewiring the neural pathways before attempting physical exposure. It's like a flight simulator for your nervous system.</p>
                    
                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <strong>The 50% Rule:</strong> Even if you only reduce pain amplification by 50%, that could mean going from an 8 to a 4 - from disabled to functional. Don't aim for perfection, aim for improvement.
                    </div>
