            <!-- Day 20 -->
            <div class="day-card" id="day20">
                <div class="day-header">
                    <span class="day-title">Day 20: First Tiny Physical Exposure</span>
                    <span class="day-date">Week 3, Day 6</span>
                </div>
                
                <div class="day-theme">
                    <h4>Today's Focus: From Imagination to Reality - Baby Steps</h4>
                    <p>The bridge from mental to physical reconditioning.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="education-section">
                    <h4>📚 Graded Exposure: The Gold Standard</h4>
                    <p>By starting with tiny exposures and gradually increasing, you give your brain hundreds of corrective experiences. Each time you do a feared activity without catastrophe, neural pathways rewire. Start so small that success is guaranteed.</p>
                    
                    <div class="key-concept">
                        <strong>Success Redefined:</strong> Success is NOT being pain-free during exposure. Success is doing it despite sensations, teaching your brain that the activity itself is safe. Symptoms may arise - that's okay. You're teaching your brain they're not dangerous.
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="exercises-section">
                    <h4>Today's Exercises</h4>
                    
                    <div class="exercise-item">
                        <div class="exercise-header">
                            <span class="exercise-title">Pre-Exposure Preparation</span>
                            <span class="exercise-time">10 min</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <p><strong>Choose your tiny exposure (30 seconds to 1 minute max!):</strong></p>
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li>Sitting in a chair for 30 seconds</li>
                                <li>Walking 10-20 steps</li>
                                <li>Gentle pelvic tilt for 10 seconds</li>
                                <li>Standing for 1 minute</li>
                                <li>Climbing 3 stairs</li>
                            </ul>
                            
                            <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Write your commitment:</strong> "I will do [activity] for [duration] to teach my brain it's safe. If symptoms arise, I'll remind myself they're not dangerous. Success is doing it, not being symptom-free."</p>
                            
                            <div class="checkbox-wrapper">
                                <input type="checkbox" id="day20-prep">
                                <label for="day20-prep">Prepared for exposure</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="exercise-item">
                        <div class="exercise-header">
                            <span class="exercise-title">The Physical Exposure</span>
                            <span class="exercise-time">10 min</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <div class="provocative-box" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d4edda, #c3e6cb); border-color: #28a745;">
                                <h5 style="color: #155724;">Your Brave Moment</h5>
                                
                                <p><strong>Step 1: Imagine it going well (1 min)</strong></p>
                                <p>See yourself doing it comfortably</p>
                                
                                <p><strong>Step 2: Set intention</strong></p>
                                <p>"I'm doing this to rewire my brain, not to test my pain"</p>
                                
                                <p><strong>Step 3: DO IT! (30 sec - 1 min)</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Focus on: "I'm teaching my brain this is safe"</li>
                                    <li>If symptoms arise: "Hello symptoms, you can't hurt me"</li>
                                    <li>Breathe normally, don't brace</li>
                                </ul>
                                
                                <p><strong>Step 4: Celebrate immediately!</strong></p>
                                <p>"I DID IT! My brain is learning!"</p>
                                
                                <p><strong>Step 5: Track aftermath</strong></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>How do you feel emotionally? (proud? scared? excited?)</li>
                                    <li>What are symptoms doing? (same? more? less?)</li>
                                    <li>Remember: Any outcome is good data</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="checkbox-wrapper">
                                <input type="checkbox" id="day20-exposure">
                                <label for="day20-exposure">COMPLETED MY FIRST PHYSICAL EXPOSURE!</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="exercise-item">
                        <div class="exercise-header">
                            <span class="exercise-title">Integration & Emotional Processing</span>
                            <span class="exercise-time">15 min</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="exercise-content">
                            <p><strong>Journal about this huge milestone:</strong></p>
                            
                            <ol>
                                <li>What emotions came up during exposure?</li>
                                <li>Did the catastrophe you imagined happen?</li>
                                <li>What did your "protector" (pain) do?</li>
                                <li>How is this evidence your brain can change?</li>
                                <li>What would you tell someone else attempting this?</li>
                            </ol>
                            
                            <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>If symptoms increased:</strong> "This is normal! My brain is testing the new pattern. With repetition, it will learn."</p>
                            
                            <p><strong>If symptoms stayed same/decreased:</strong> "My brain is already learning! This will get easier each time."</p>
                            
